{"index": 21, "en_name": "1 Maccabees", "local_name": "", "chapters": [], "metadata": [{"title": "Author", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "—Although the author of 1 Maccabees never identifies himself, it may reasonably be assumed that he was an orthodox Jew familiar with both the geography and the topography of Judea."}]}, {"title": "Date", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "—About 104 BC, according to the last two verses of the book ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "16:23", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap16-23", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 16, "verse": 23}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ", "}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "24", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap16-24", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 16, "verse": 24}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " The work was compiled during or shortly after the reign of John Hyrcanus I (134–104 BC), the high priest and ruler of Israel."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " It covers the period from the reign of Antiochus IV Epiphanes (175–164 BC) to the succession of John Hyrcanus."}]}, {"title": "Major Theme", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "—"}, {"style": "ITALIC", "text": "God's deliverance of Israel during the Jewish Wars."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": "God's deliverance of Israel during the Jewish Wars."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " The author makes it clear that God chose the Hasmonean family as the instrument of his deliverance ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "5:62", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap5-62", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 5, "verse": 62}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " Their primary objective was the rededication of the temple ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "4:36–61", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap4-36", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 4, "verse": 36}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": "), an event still celebrated by Jews everywhere as the festival of Hanukkah, from the Hebrew word for “dedication.”"}]}, {"title": "Background", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "—First Maccabees was originally written in Hebrew and was probably called “The Hasmoneans,” after Mattathias of the house of Hashmon ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "2:1", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap2-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 2, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " It was Mattathias who began the Jewish revolt with the help of his five sons."}, {"style": "NONE", "text": " The bulk of the book recounts Judah's war against Antiochus IV, the Seleucid ruler who tried to force Hellenism upon the Jews."}]}, {"title": "Outline", "content_parts": [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Outline"}], "list": [[{"style": "NONE", "text": "Prologue: The Hellenistic Empire from Alexander to Antiochus IV ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "1:1–64", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap1-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 1, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "The Hasmonean (Maccabean) Revolt ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "2:1–4:61", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap2-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 2, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Jewish Expeditions against Neighboring Tribes ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "5:1–68", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap5-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 5, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Lysias Usurps the Throne ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "6:1–63", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap6-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 6, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "The Reign of Demetrius I Soter ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "7:1–50", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap7-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 7, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "The Alliance between the Jews and the Romans ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "8:1–31", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap8-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 8, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Jonathan Succeeds Judas ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "9:1–73", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap9-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 9, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "The Rise and Fall of Alexander Balas ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "10:1–11:19", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap10-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 10, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Demetrius II Betrays the Jews ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "11:20–53", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap11-20", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 11, "verse": 20}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "Trypho and the Reign of Antiochus VI ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "11:54–12:53", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap11-54", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 11, "verse": 54}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}], [{"style": "NONE", "text": "The Emergence of the Jewish Nation under Simon ("}, {"style": "CROSS_REF", "text": "13:1–16:24", "target": {"href": "1Maccabees.html#M1acc_vchap13-1", "book_file": "1Maccabees", "chapter": 13, "verse": 1}}, {"style": "NONE", "text": ")"}]]}]}